Class BarcodeImage

java.lang.Object
BarcodeImage
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Cloneable
class BarcodeImage
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
BarcodeImage is meant to retrieve and store 2D patterns. Does not perform image shift or white space removal.
Author:
rshum

      public BarcodeImage​(java.lang.String[] strData)

  • Method Details

    • getPixel

      public boolean getPixel​(int row, int col)
      Returns true if imageData[row][col] is true ('*' present at corresponding location in input string). Based on spec, will return false if element is false or null.
      Parameters:
      row - value of row of target element in imageData[][]
      col - value of column of target element in imageData[][]
      Returns:
      TRUE if element is true. FALSE if element is anything else

    • setPixel

      public boolean setPixel​(int row, int col, boolean value)
      Sets boolean value of imageData[row][col].
      Parameters:
      row - value of row of target element in imageData[][]
      col - value of column of target element in imageData[][]
      value - boolean value that element should be set to
      Returns:
      TRUE if element successfully changed. FALSE if out of bounds.
